# Java SE 7+ HttpHeaders. Read/write/store http headers. MIT (c) 2020-2021 miktim@mail.ru

Release notes:
  - the header names (keys) ara case-insensitive;
  - multiple values are stored on a comma separated string;
  - the HTTP request/status line is accessed using constants.

package org.miktim;

Overview:

  Class HttpHeaders;
    Constructor:
      HttpHeaders();
      
    Constants:
      static String REQUEST_LINE; // 
      static String STATUS_LINE = REQUEST_LINE; //
      
    Methods:
      HttpHeaders set(String key, String value); // create or overwrite header value
      HttpHeaders add(String key, String value); // add comma separated value or create header
      String get(String key);
      boolean containsKey(String key);
      Set<String> keySet(); // returns set of header names without request/status line
      HttpHeaders read(InputStream is) throws IOException;
      void write(OutputStream os) throws IOException; // !set request/status line before writing

Usage:
  See WebSocket package WsConnection class handshakeClient, handshakeServer methods.
